Linux
=====

Install the following packages via your distribution package manager:

* python (tested with 2.7)
* numpy (tested with 1.6.2)
* pyside (tested with 1.1.1)
* python-opengl (tested with 3.0.1) 
* beautiful soup 4 (tested with 4.1.0)

You will have to build and install the following packages from source:

* pyv8 (http://code.google.com/p/pyv8/)
* pyftgl (http://code.google.com/p/pyftgl/) (tested with 0.5c)

After that, just unpack the madparts tar file and run the madscripts
script contained in it.

Hopefully in the future madparts and it's dependencies will be packaged
to be part of your favorite linux distrubution.

